    "body": "For anyone looking into this, I found another glitch, this time on Debian Linux.\n\nHere;s the relevant `directory` config:\n```toml\n[directory]\nstyle = \"bg:peach fg:crust\"\n# repo_root_style = \"bold bg:peach fg:white\"\nformat = '[ $path ]($style)[$read_only]($read_only_style)'\ntruncation_length = 3  # default\ntruncation_symbol = '…'\n```\n\nWith the `repo_root_style` commented out (as shown above), the prompt displays as expected, see the first line below:\n\n<img width=\"350\" height=\"170\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4a043ba4-38c4-4a04-b38e-9a61995afcf9\" />\n\nHowever, with the `repo_root_style` line active, the repo color is white, as expected, BUT notice the space in front of '...' has disappeared, and the trailing space is not styled at all!\n\nHopefully these two scenarios give some clues for a fix.",
